OverHistory.NewCommentry: Mitchell Starc to Yashasvi Jaiswal Wicket
OverHistory.Commentry: Mitchell Starc bowling to Yashasvi Jaiswal, full length ball, pitching on leg stump, Yashasvi Jaiswal plays an aggressive front foot flick WICKET Yashasvi Jaiswal lbw Mitchell Starc (India 0 Runs for 1 wickets)
OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
BANG! FIRST BALL STRIKES! Mitchell Starc bowling to Yashasvi Jaiswal, full length ball, pitching on leg stump, Yashasvi Jaiswal caught plumb in front and he knows it, walking straight away! Ball tracking shows three reds, and India lose their first before troubling the scorers. 

 WICKET Yashasvi Jaiswal lbw Mitchell Starc (India 0 Runs for 1 wickets)

OverHistory.Commentry: Mitchell Starc bowling to Ravichandran Ashwin, yorker ball, pitching on leg stump, Ravichandran Ashwin plays a forward defensive shot WICKET Ravichandran Ashwin lbw Mitchell Starc (India 141 Runs for 7 wickets), Appeal from the fielding side
OverHistory.UPDCommentry:
PLUMB AND GONE Mitchell Starc bowling to Ravichandran Ashwin, yorker ball, pitching on leg stump, Ravichandran Ashwin caught in a tangle - moves across early, loses balance, and that toe-crusher's too good! The ball curves in late, Ashwin can't get his bat down in time, and it hammers into the front pad. Up goes the finger, and though he reviews hopefully, three reds confirm what everyone knew - that was crashing into middle! 

 WICKET Ravichandran Ashwin lbw Mitchell Starc (India 141 Runs for 7 wickets)

INDIA FINISH WITH 175 AND WITH A LEAD OF 18 RUNS Scott Boland bowling to Mohammed Siraj, short of good length ball, pitching outside off stump, Mohammed Siraj backs away for a wild swing. He only manages a bottom edge, sending the ball skyward. Head,judges it perfectly and completes a good catch near mid-on. Boland finishes with three wickets, and Australia need 19 runs to level the series!

WICKET Mohammed Siraj c Travis Head b Scott Boland (India 175 Runs for 10 wickets)
